title: Vikings net seventh win in shutout of Golden Bucks
text:
Vikings net seventh win in shutout of Golden Bucks Ogden tallies game-winning goal in Heal Point-worth victory By Staff | Oct 08, 2015 
Searsport â€” The Searsport girls high school soccer team has ascended the Class D ranks, which continued on Wednesday, Oct. 7 as the Vikings hosted area-rival Bucksport. 
The two sides battled back-and-forth through the 80 minutes, but, in the end, it was a goal by senior Melinda Ogden that proved the difference in a 1-0 shutout win for the home-standing Vikings. 
Photos from this game will appear later with this story. 
Ogden creased the net with 9:44 remaining in the first half. 
Brooklynn Alberts made one save on four shotsin goal for Searsport, while Tessa Soloman made 10 saves on 14 shots in net for Bucksport. The Vikings held a 6-3 edge in corner kicks. 
In the Maine Principals' Association Heal Point Standings for Class D South, Searsport (7-3, 37.6531 points) is fourth, while Richmond (8-1, 68.8584 points) is first in the 10-team region. The top seven teams qualify for the playoffs.
